HEADWORD: Subaudition
<hw>Sub`au*di"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>subauditio</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of understanding, or
supplying, something not expressed; also, that which is so understood or
supplied.</def> <rj><au>Trench.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

